## File-by-File Reference

---

### `app/` — FastAPI Backend

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| [main.py](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/main.py) | Creates the FastAPI `app` instance. Registers CORS middleware, mounts the API router at `/api/v1`, and exposes the root health endpoint. Entry point for `uvicorn`. |
| [api/schemas.py](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/api/schemas.py) | All Pydantic models: [SessionInput](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/api/schemas.py#39-45), [TelemetryInput](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/api/schemas.py#16-24), [NLPInput](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/api/schemas.py#26-37), [PredictionResponse](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/api/schemas.py#72-85), [SessionSummaryResponse](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/api/schemas.py#93-105). These are the strict data contracts between clients and the backend. |
| [api/routes.py](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/api/routes.py) | Five endpoint groups: health check, `/process` (main pipeline), `/session/{id}/summary`, `/session/{id}/reset`, `/sessions` (list). Each route calls the five core module registries in sequence. |
| [core/config.py](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/config.py) | Dataclasses for [CIIConfig](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/config.py#11-22) (weights α,β,γ,δ), [PredictorConfig](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/config.py#24-32) (thresholds), [ControllerConfig](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/config.py#34-41) (difficulty bounds), [LSTMConfig](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/config.py#43-53) (hyperparams). A [SystemConfig](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/config.py#62-74) singleton is imported app-wide so there is exactly one source of truth for all parameters. |
| [core/telemetry.py](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/telemetry.py) | [PerformanceTracker](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/telemetry.py#28-102): maintains a rolling deque of composite performance scores per session and returns D(t) as a z-score. [TelemetryRegistry](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/telemetry.py#108-131): session-keyed dictionary of trackers for multi-session support. |
| [core/nlp.py](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/nlp.py) | [NLPExtractor](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/nlp.py#64-203): rule-based lexicon for polarity and intensity (swap [_compute_polarity()](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/nlp.py#111-139) with a RoBERTa call for production). Maintains sentiment trend history. [NLPRegistry](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/nlp.py#209-222): session management. |
| [core/emotional_dynamics.py](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/emotional_dynamics.py) | [EmotionalDynamicsEngine](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/emotional_dynamics.py#50-125): stateful per-session engine. Computes M(t)=P·I, A(t)=ΔM/Δt, CII(t) at every call to `.process()`. Returns [EmotionalState](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/emotional_dynamics.py#26-44) dataclass with `.as_feature_vector()` for LSTM input. |
| [core/predictor.py](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/predictor.py) | [RuleBasedPredictor](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/predictor.py#115-158): threshold policy. [SimulatedLSTMPredictor](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/predictor.py#54-109): EWA + linear trend proxy (no PyTorch needed). [CognitiveStatePredictor](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/predictor.py#164-208): blends both 60/40. [PredictorRegistry](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/predictor.py#214-225): session management. |
| [core/controller.py](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/controller.py) | [AdaptiveDifficultyController](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/cognitive_instability_prototype.py#250-298): applies action (decrease/maintain/increase), scales step by \|CII\|, computes RL reward, logs history. [session_summary()](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/controller.py#158-179) returns aggregate analytics. [ControllerRegistry](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/controller.py#185-200): session management. |
| [models/lstm.py](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/models/lstm.py) | [CIILSTMPredictor(nn.Module)](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/models/lstm.py#45-120): 2-layer LSTM → Dropout → Linear(2) → Sigmoid. [CIIDataset](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/models/lstm.py#126-149): sliding-window PyTorch Dataset. [LSTMTrainer](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/models/lstm.py#155-201): training loop with BCE loss and Adam optimizer. Protected by `try/except ImportError` so the system works without PyTorch. |

---

### `data/` — Data Assets

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `raw/telemetry_logs/` | Game engine exports — one CSV or JSON file per session. Contains: session_id, timestamp, deaths, retries, score_delta, reaction_time_ms, input_speed. Exactly as received from the game client — never modified. |
| `raw/player_text/` | Raw player chat or voice-to-text transcripts, one file per session. Preserved in original form for NLP reprocessing. |
| `processed/features.csv` | Feature-engineered dataset built by `utils/preprocessing.py`. Columns: `[session_id, timestep, polarity, intensity, perf_dev, intent_gap, momentum, accel, cii, state_label]`. Input to all classifiers. |
| `processed/sequences.npy` | Pre-built LSTM input sequences as a NumPy array of shape [(N, W, 5)](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/models/lstm.py#111-120) where W=10 (window) and 5 = `[CII, M, A, D, G]`. Avoids rebuilding windows on every training run. |
| `labeled/labels.csv` | Ground truth cognitive state labels fused from: self-report (GEQ), behavioral annotation (Cohen's κ ≥ 0.70), and physiological signals. Three output columns: `[is_frustrated, is_bored, is_engaged]`. |
| `labeled/annotation_guide.md` | Step-by-step protocol for human annotators: coding scheme, OCSGA definitions, inter-rater resolution rules, and examples for edge cases. |
| `splits/train.csv`, `val.csv`, `test.csv` | Stratified splits of `features.csv` by player ID (not by timestep) to prevent data leakage across sessions. |

---

### `models/` — Saved Artifacts

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `checkpoints/lstm_best.pt` | PyTorch checkpoint saved at the epoch with lowest validation loss. Contains `state_dict` and `cfg` object. Loaded by `CIILSTMPredictor.load()`. |
| `checkpoints/lstm_final.pt` | Checkpoint from the final training epoch (may not be the best — kept for reproducibility). |
| `configs/lstm_v1.json` | Snapshot of hyperparameters used in experiment v1: input_dim, hidden_dim, num_layers, dropout, lr, batch_size, seq_len. Allows exact reproduction. |
| `reports/training_curves.png` | Loss-per-epoch plot generated by `notebooks/03_lstm_training.ipynb`. |
| `reports/evaluation_report.json` | Structured JSON with F1 (macro, weighted), ROC-AUC, MCC, and Cohen's κ for all 6 models (5 baselines + proposed). Consumed by Streamlit analytics tab. |

---

### `services/` — Standalone Service Layer

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `data_collector.py` | Polls the game engine API at configurable intervals, normalizes telemetry format, and appends rows to `data/raw/telemetry_logs/`. Runs as a background process or daemon. |
| `nlp_service.py` | Production NLP inference server. Loads RoBERTa / VADER at startup (once), accepts text via a local queue, returns [(polarity, intensity)](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/models/lstm.py#111-120). Decoupled from FastAPI request cycle to avoid latency. |
| `lstm_inference.py` | Loads `lstm_best.pt` at startup, accepts feature sequences from a queue, returns [(p_frus, p_bore)](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/models/lstm.py#111-120). Used as a drop-in replacement for [SimulatedLSTMPredictor](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/predictor.py#54-109) in [predictor.py](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/predictor.py). |
| `session_manager.py` | Manages the full lifecycle of player sessions: creation, heartbeat tracking, idle timeout, memory cleanup. Exposes session health metrics for system monitoring. |

---

### `utils/` — Shared Utilities

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `preprocessing.py` | `build_feature_matrix()`: reads raw CSVs and runs full CII pipeline offline to produce `processed/features.csv`. `build_lstm_sequences()`: sliding window assembler → `sequences.npy`. `normalize()`: min-max and z-score scalers. |
| `metrics.py` | Pure-Python implementations of evaluation metrics: `f1_macro()`, `f1_weighted()`, `roc_auc_ovr()`, `mcc()`, `cohens_kappa()`. Used in notebooks and evaluation scripts without scikit-learn dependency. |
| `visualization.py` | `plot_cii_trajectory()`: line chart of CII over session. `plot_state_heatmap()`: 2D heatmap of frustration/boredom probability over time. `plot_difficulty_curve()`: difficulty level timeline. All return `matplotlib.Figure` objects. |
| `logger.py` | Configures `structlog` or standard `logging` with JSON output format, log rotation, and request-ID injection. Imported by all modules via `from utils.logger import get_logger`. |
| `seed.py` | `set_seed(n)`: sets Python, NumPy, and PyTorch random seeds simultaneously. Called at the start of every training script and notebook for reproducibility. |

---

### `frontend/` — User Interfaces

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| [dashboard/app.py](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/dashboard/app.py) | Streamlit real-time dashboard. Connects to FastAPI at `localhost:8000`. Renders: CII trend line chart, player state badge, probability bars, difficulty timeline, emotional state component bars, step history table, session summary KPIs. Supports manual input and 3 pre-built auto-scenarios. |
| `static/index.html` | Standalone browser-based demo that calls the FastAPI directly from JavaScript. No build step required — suitable for quick demonstrations without Streamlit. |
| `static/style.css` | Dashboard visual styling: dark mode palette, card layout, state-color badges (red=frustrated, amber=bored, green=engaged). |
| `static/demo.js` | Fetch API wrapper for `/api/v1/process`. Renders Chart.js CII line chart and updates DOM elements with prediction results. |

---

### `tests/` — Test Suite

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `test_cii_engine.py` | Verifies M(t)=P·I, A(t)=ΔM/Δt, CII formula, weight constraint (sum=1.0), and boundary clamping behavior. |
| `test_nlp.py` | Tests polarity sign correctness for positive/negative text, intensity non-negativity, sentiment trend direction. |
| `test_telemetry.py` | Tests z-score output during warm-up, correct normalization, and per-session isolation. |
| `test_predictor.py` | Tests that frustrated input produces state=frustrated, boredom input produces state=bored, blending weights sum correctly. |
| `test_controller.py` | Tests difficulty clamping at d_min/d_max, action selection logic, reward sign for each state. |
| `test_api.py` | End-to-end FastAPI integration tests: POST /process returns 200 with correct schema, session summary returns correct aggregate. Uses `httpx.AsyncClient` with `pytest-asyncio`. |

---

### `notebooks/` — Research Notebooks

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `01_eda.ipynb` | Visualizes raw telemetry distributions, class imbalance, NLP feature correlations. Identifies outliers and informs preprocessing decisions. |
| `02_feature_engineering.ipynb` | Step-by-step derivation of M(t), A(t), D(t), CII(t) from raw data. Plots CII trajectory for each session. Validates the CII formula against human labels. |
| `03_lstm_training.ipynb` | Full LSTM training pipeline: data loading, model init, training loop, validation, checkpoint saving, evaluation against all 5 baselines. Generates `reports/`. |
| `04_rl_simulation.ipynb` | Simulates the RL controller over session trajectories. Plots reward over time, flow rate achievement, and difficulty variance. Compares rule-based vs. RL-optimized control. |

