## Scalability Notes

> [!TIP]
> **Adding a new feature:** Add it to [schemas.py](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/api/schemas.py) (input) → [telemetry.py](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/telemetry.py) or [nlp.py](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/nlp.py) (extraction) → [emotional_dynamics.py](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/emotional_dynamics.py) (integration into E(t)) → [config.py](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/config.py) (weight parameter). No other files need changing.

> [!TIP]
> **Swapping to real NLP model:** Replace only `NLPExtractor._compute_polarity()` and [_compute_intensity()](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/nlp.py#144-177) in [nlp.py](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/nlp.py). The interface — returning a [dict](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/predictor.py#127-158) with [polarity](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/api/schemas.py#33-37), [intensity](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/nlp.py#144-177), `sentiment_trend`, `intent_gap` — stays identical.

> [!TIP]
> **Enabling the real LSTM:** Set `lstm_inference.py` as a subprocess service, import `CIILSTMPredictor.load()` in [predictor.py](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/predictor.py), and replace [SimulatedLSTMPredictor](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/predictor.py#54-109). The blending logic in [CognitiveStatePredictor](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/predictor.py#164-208) is unchanged.

> [!NOTE]
> **Multi-player scaling:** Every registry ([TelemetryRegistry](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/telemetry.py#108-131), [NLPRegistry](file:///f:/B.Tech%20CSE%28AIML%29%20VIIT/SEM%206/NLP-RP/app/core/nlp.py#209-222), etc.) is already keyed by `session_id`. Replace the in-memory dicts with Redis-backed stores for distributed multi-server deployment.
